15:28.884 --> 15:32.322
♪ JUST LIVING IT UP
♪ JUST LIVING THE DREAM

15:32.453 --> 15:35.499
♪ WHEN I GET A LITTLE CRAZY

15:39.068 --> 15:40.287
-YEAH!

16:43.176 --> 16:44.264
-ARE YOUR SETS ALL DONE?

16:44.394 --> 16:45.221
-YEAH.

16:47.354 --> 16:48.398
-WOMAN: BYE!
-JORDAN: SEE YA!

16:48.529 --> 16:49.443
-WOMAN: BYE.

16:51.097 --> 16:51.880
-C.J.: SEE YOU, GUYS.

16:52.011 --> 16:52.924
-WOMAN: HEY, C.J.!

16:54.143 --> 16:55.057
[SIGHING]

16:55.666 --> 16:56.885
-THIS IS A WEIRD ONE.

16:57.016 --> 16:57.973
-WELL, IT LOOKS
LIKE WE'RE GONNA BE

16:58.104 --> 16:59.105
THE LAST ONES OUT OF HERE.

16:59.931 --> 17:01.020
-I'M ALMOST DONE.

17:02.760 --> 17:04.022
-THE PHANTOM LIFEGUARD?

17:04.153 --> 17:05.023
-YEAH, THAT'S WHAT
WE'RE CALLING HIM.

17:05.154 --> 17:06.634
-JORDAN: WHAT'S THAT?

17:06.763 --> 17:07.548
-UM, HE SAVED A LITTLE
BOY'S LIFE AT THE PIER

17:07.678 --> 17:09.028
BY THE OLD POWER PLANT.

17:09.157 --> 17:10.550
-DO YOU KNOW WHO HE IS?

17:10.681 --> 17:13.118
-NO, THE KID SAID
HE'S GROSS, HE'S UGLY,

17:13.249 --> 17:15.077
HE'S GNARLY, HIS HANDS
ARE ALL BANDAGED,

17:15.208 --> 17:16.861
HE WEARS A MASK.

17:17.645 --> 17:19.080
HEY, IF YOU'RE NOT
DOING ANYTHING TONIGHT,

17:19.212 --> 17:20.126
DO YOU WANT TO GO TO THE
PIER AND CHECK IT OUT?

17:20.256 --> 17:21.431
SEE IF WE FIND ANYTHING?

17:21.561 --> 17:22.519
-OH, C.J.,
I'M SORRY, I CAN'T.

17:22.650 --> 17:24.391
I'M ALREADY LATE FOR A DATE.

17:24.521 --> 17:26.567
BUT UH, I'LL BE HAPPY TO CHECK
IT OUT WITH YOU TOMORROW.

17:26.696 --> 17:28.047
CAN YOU CLOSE UP ON YOUR OWN?

17:28.176 --> 17:29.700
-SURE.
-OK.

17:29.831 --> 17:30.788
SEE YA.

17:33.052 --> 17:33.922
-LOOKS LIKE I'LL
BE DOING EVERYTHING

17:34.053 --> 17:35.358
ON MY OWN THIS WEEKEND.

17:40.407 --> 17:42.539
[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

18:46.821 --> 18:48.823
[GRUNTING]

19:07.581 --> 19:09.800
[PANTING]

21:50.874 --> 21:51.832
-OH!

21:51.962 --> 21:53.747
-STAY THERE, YOU'RE HURT.

21:53.877 --> 21:55.052
DON'T TRY TO MOVE.

21:55.183 --> 21:56.837
-WHO'S THERE?

21:56.967 --> 21:57.794
-DON'T BE AFRAID.

21:59.013 --> 22:00.754
-C.J.: WHERE AM I?
-MY HOME.

22:01.320 --> 22:03.060
YOU HAD
AN ACCIDENT AT THE PIER.

22:03.191 --> 22:05.236
ONE OF THE PYLONS FELL OVER.

22:05.367 --> 22:06.716
-HOW LONG HAVE I BEEN HERE?

22:06.847 --> 22:07.848
-ALL NIGHT.

22:07.978 --> 22:09.110
-I HAVE TO GO.

22:09.240 --> 22:10.720
I HAVE TO GET OUT OF HERE.

22:11.373 --> 22:12.983
OW!
[CROW SQUAWKS]

22:14.333 --> 22:15.464
-SHH.

22:17.553 --> 22:18.902
-DON'T HURT ME!

22:27.215 --> 22:28.477
-I DON'T THINK IT'S BROKEN,

22:29.173 --> 22:30.566
BUT DON'T TRY
TO MOVE IT, ANYWAY.

22:31.698 --> 22:32.786
I SUPPOSE I SHOULD
HAVE TAKEN YOU

22:32.916 --> 22:35.136
TO THE HOSPITAL, BUT UH...

22:35.266 --> 22:36.485
-YOU TOOK CARE OF ME.

22:36.616 --> 22:38.139
-YES.

22:39.793 --> 22:40.837
-YOU'RE VERY GENTLE.

22:40.968 --> 22:42.186
-CROW: HELLO!

22:43.231 --> 22:44.754
-I'M SORRY, I'VE BEEN RUDE.

22:44.885 --> 22:46.190
THIS IS MAX.

22:47.496 --> 22:50.107
-HI, MAX. I'M C.J.
-MAX: HELLO!

22:50.238 --> 22:51.152
-AND...

22:52.327 --> 22:53.284
-MY NAME.

22:55.417 --> 22:56.287
AIDEN.

22:57.550 --> 22:58.855
AIDEN MASTERS.

23:00.727 --> 23:01.858
-HELLO, AIDEN.

23:07.560 --> 23:09.431
YOU'RE THE ONE WHO SAVED
THE LITTLE BOY, AREN'T YOU?

23:10.737 --> 23:11.694
-YES.

23:12.956 --> 23:13.827
-WHO ARE YOU?

23:14.784 --> 23:15.872
-YOU MEAN WHO WAS I?

23:34.238 --> 23:37.111
-JORDAN! HAVE YOU SEEN C.J.?
-NO, I HAVEN'T.

23:37.241 --> 23:39.243
-WHAT TIME'S HER SHIFT?
-WELL, IT STARTED AN HOUR AGO,

23:39.374 --> 23:40.984
BUT SHE HASN'T SHOWN UP YET.

23:41.115 --> 23:42.551
THAT'S WHY I'M CALLING HER.

23:44.292 --> 23:45.075
THERE'S NO ANSWER.

23:45.206 --> 23:46.337
[SIGHING]

23:46.468 --> 23:48.209
-I JUST GOT BACK
FROM SURFING.

23:48.949 --> 23:51.517
SHE WASN'T AT HOME,
HER BED HASN'T BEEN SLEPT IN.

23:51.647 --> 23:53.823
SHE DIDN'T COME HOME
LAST NIGHT, JORDAN.

23:53.954 --> 23:55.651
AND NOW SHE'S LATE FOR WORK?

23:55.782 --> 23:56.739
SHE'S NEVER LATE.

23:56.870 --> 23:57.958
SHE'S ALWAYS EARLY.

24:02.615 --> 24:04.573
"WE LOVED WITH A LOVE
THAT WAS MORE THAN LOVE,

24:04.704 --> 24:06.706
"I AND MY ANNABEL LEE.

24:06.836 --> 24:08.447
"AND NEITHER THE
ANGELS IN HEAVEN ABOVE

24:08.577 --> 24:10.536
"NOR THE DEMONS
DOWN UNDER THE SEA

24:10.666 --> 24:12.233
"CAN EVER DISSEVER
MY SOUL FROM THE SOUL

24:12.363 --> 24:14.235
OF THE BEAUTIFUL ANNABEL LEE."

24:24.985 --> 24:26.508
-WHERE'D YOU GET
ALL THESE BOOKS?

24:26.639 --> 24:28.858
-WELL, MY FATHER WAS
AN ENGLISH PROFESSOR.

24:29.555 --> 24:31.426
HE LEFT ME HIS
COLLECTION WHEN HE DIED.

24:32.732 --> 24:35.517
THEY ARE
MY ONLY COMPANIONSHIP,

24:36.344 --> 24:37.432
OTHER THAN MAX.

24:38.781 --> 24:39.695
-HOW'D YOU FIND MAX?

24:40.217 --> 24:42.568
-OH, UH, HE FOUND ME.

24:43.699 --> 24:47.181
I GET SO TIRED OF
SEEING THE FEAR AND...

24:47.834 --> 24:49.575
PITY IN PEOPLE'S EYES,

24:50.184 --> 24:52.360
SO I QUIT LOOKING INTO THEM.

24:54.057 --> 24:55.537
MAX ACCEPTS ME AS I AM.

24:56.712 --> 24:59.062
-ANNABEL LEE, ANNABEL LEE.

24:59.193 --> 25:00.107
[SQUAWKING]

25:01.151 --> 25:02.370
-MAX MAN, PLEASE.

25:02.501 --> 25:04.285
-MAX: ANNABEL LEE!
-AIDEN: SHH!

25:04.894 --> 25:05.895
SHH!

25:06.026 --> 25:07.157
-AIDEN.

25:08.202 --> 25:09.116
LOOK AT ME.

25:11.335 --> 25:13.512
THE POEM AND THE FLOWERS,

25:13.642 --> 25:14.513
IT WAS YOU, WASN'T IT?

25:18.386 --> 25:19.430
THE WOMAN IN THIS PHOTOGRAPH,

25:19.561 --> 25:20.649
SHE LOOKS SO MUCH LIKE ME.

25:21.694 --> 25:22.521
AND THE MAN--

25:22.651 --> 25:23.522
-IS WHO I USED TO BE.

25:28.396 --> 25:30.180
YOU REMINDED ME
SO MUCH OF HER.

25:31.225 --> 25:33.532
I NEVER THOUGHT I COULD
FEEL THAT WAY AGAIN.

25:38.841 --> 25:40.147
-C.J.: WHAT HAPPENED?

25:40.669 --> 25:41.627
-OH.

25:43.193 --> 25:44.281
SHE DIED.

25:46.240 --> 25:47.937
EVERYTHING DIED.

25:51.071 --> 25:52.551
-TRUST ME.

25:53.813 --> 25:54.988
I WON'T HURT YOU.

25:59.558 --> 26:01.560
-IT'S BEEN YEARS SINCE
ANYONE HAS TOUCHED ME.

26:10.786 --> 26:12.788
I'D FORGOTTEN
WHAT IT FELT LIKE.

26:24.408 --> 26:25.888
-BILLY: WHOA, LOOK AT HIM.

26:26.497 --> 26:27.281
THIS DUDE'S AWESOME!

26:27.411 --> 26:28.848
-BRETT: YEAH.

26:28.978 --> 26:30.066
YEAH, WE OUGHT TO CALL
THE COPS OR SOMETHING.

26:30.197 --> 26:31.372
-NO WAY, MAN!

26:31.502 --> 26:32.852
WE'RE GONNA FILM HIS CAPTURE.

26:34.070 --> 26:36.116
-WHAT ARE YOU, CRAZY?
THIS GUY COULD BE DANGEROUS.

26:36.899 --> 26:38.466
-SO GET WILL AND
BOBBY D. TO GO WITH US.

26:38.597 --> 26:39.946
IT'D BE FOUR AGAINST ONE.

26:40.076 --> 26:41.469
WE'LL CATCH THE MONSTER,

26:41.600 --> 26:43.471
RESCUE THE BEAUTIFUL
DAMSEL IN DISTRESS.

26:43.602 --> 26:45.952
HEH. HEROES AND
MILLIONAIRES. FILM AT 11.

26:46.082 --> 26:47.693
-NO, I, I AM NO HERO, OK?

26:47.823 --> 26:48.694
I'M NOT GOING.

26:51.044 --> 26:52.698
-THAT'S BAD, DUDE.

26:52.828 --> 26:54.090
WE'LL JUST HAVE TO SPLIT UP
YOUR SHARE OF THE MONEY.

26:58.051 --> 26:59.530
-"FOR THE MOON NEVER BEAMS

26:59.661 --> 27:01.184
"WITHOUT BRINGING ME DREAMS

27:01.315 --> 27:02.664
"OF THE BEAUTIFUL ANNABEL LEE.

27:04.100 --> 27:06.146
"AND THE STARS NEVER RISE,

27:06.668 --> 27:08.496
"BUT I FEEL THE BRIGHT EYES

27:08.627 --> 27:10.629
"OF THE BEAUTIFUL ANNABEL LEE.

27:11.499 --> 27:13.806
"AND SO, ALL THE NIGHT-TIDE,

27:15.155 --> 27:17.636
"I LIE DOWN BY THE
SIDE OF MY DARLING,

27:18.985 --> 27:19.942
"MY DARLING,

27:21.640 --> 27:23.772
"MY LIFE AND MY BRIDE,

27:25.731 --> 27:27.646
"IN HER SEPULCHER
THERE BY THE SEA.

27:28.168 --> 27:32.259
IN HER TOMB
BY THE SOUNDING SEA."

27:34.435 --> 27:36.350
-"IN HER TOMB BY
THE SOUNDING SEA."

27:40.397 --> 27:41.355
OH, NO!

27:42.486 --> 27:43.879
-EXCUSE ME,
THERE'S THIS PROBLEM

27:44.010 --> 27:44.880
YOU REALLY NEED TO KNOW ABOUT--

27:45.011 --> 27:46.577
-WHAT KIND OF PROBLEM?

27:46.708 --> 27:47.753
-WELL, THERE'S THIS FREAKY
GUY DOWN BY THE PIER.

27:47.883 --> 27:48.841
HE TOOK THIS GIRL.

27:48.971 --> 27:49.885
-WHAT'D SHE LOOK LIKE?

27:50.016 --> 27:51.452
-BLONDE, SHE'S BEAUTIFUL.

27:51.582 --> 27:53.280
-WHERE'D HE TAKE HER?

27:53.410 --> 27:54.542
-WELL, HE CARRIED HER OFF
TO THE ABANDONED POWER PLANT.

27:54.673 --> 27:56.065
-HEY THANKS, MAN!
-SURE. I SAW--

27:56.196 --> 27:57.893
IN FACT, I GOT IT ON VIDEO TAPE!

27:58.546 --> 28:00.113
-POE WAS MISUNDERSTOOD
AS A POET.

28:01.331 --> 28:03.986
MOST THOUGHT HE WAS
A MACABRE AND MORBID WRITER.

28:04.900 --> 28:06.859
-"ANNABEL LEE" IS
BEAUTIFUL AND ROMANTIC.

28:07.947 --> 28:08.991
AND VERY SAD.

28:10.558 --> 28:13.561
-FOR POE, THE DEATH
OF A BEAUTIFUL WOMAN

28:13.692 --> 28:15.215
WAS THE MOST TRAGIC,

28:15.345 --> 28:18.131
MOST POETIC TOPIC
IN THE WORLD.

28:18.261 --> 28:20.307
HE LOST HIS WIFE.

28:21.003 --> 28:22.439
HER DEATH TORMENTED HIM.

28:22.570 --> 28:25.138
HE COULD NEVER ACCEPT
THE FACT

28:25.268 --> 28:29.359
THAT SHE WOULD COME
BACK HIM NEVERMORE.

28:30.534 --> 28:32.667
-MAX: [SQUAWKS] NEVERMORE!

28:36.279 --> 28:37.672
-MITCH: HEY, HEY,
WHAT'S GOING ON?

28:37.803 --> 28:39.021
-MITCH, SAM, THANK
GOD YOU GUYS ARE BACK.

28:39.152 --> 28:40.501
HE'S GONNA KILL C.J.

28:40.631 --> 28:42.242
-WHAT?
-THE ABANDONED POWER PLANT.

28:42.372 --> 28:43.852
WE GOTTA GET THERE FAST!

28:53.601 --> 28:54.950
-AIDEN, TELL ME ABOUT HER.

28:56.996 --> 28:59.389
-I HAD EVERYTHING ANY
MAN COULD EVER WANT.

29:00.303 --> 29:01.435
I HAD CATHERINE.

29:02.392 --> 29:03.742
AND WE FOUND LOVE.

29:07.267 --> 29:08.659
WE HAD OUR DREAM HOUSE.

29:10.226 --> 29:11.793
WE WERE PLANNING
ON HAVING A BABY.

29:14.056 --> 29:15.362
EVERYTHING WAS WONDERFUL,

29:15.492 --> 29:16.755
AND WE THOUGHT IT WOULD BE

29:16.885 --> 29:18.191
FOR THE REST OF OUR LIVES.

29:24.371 --> 29:26.199
CATHERINE WAS ONLY
BEING ROMANTIC.

29:29.289 --> 29:31.291
SHE KNEW HOW
I LOVED CANDLELIGHT.

29:32.335 --> 29:35.774
A CURTAIN MUST HAVE
BLOWN IN THE WIND.

29:38.080 --> 29:39.386
IT CAUGHT AFLAME.

29:43.912 --> 29:45.174
WHEN I PULLED UP IN
FRONT OF THE HOUSE,

29:45.305 --> 29:46.480
IT WAS ALREADY ON FIRE.

29:47.786 --> 29:50.789
[SCREAMING]

29:54.444 --> 29:57.317
CATHERINE!

30:02.844 --> 30:04.324
NO!

30:05.934 --> 30:07.501
MY GOD!

30:07.631 --> 30:09.024
GOD, NO!

30:10.199 --> 30:12.114
[SCREAMING]

30:13.420 --> 30:14.900
I LOST
EVERYTHING THAT NIGHT.

30:19.339 --> 30:21.036
THE PAIN OF MY BURNS
WAS NOTHING

30:21.167 --> 30:23.169
COMPARED TO THE PAIN
OF LOSING CATHERINE.

30:25.519 --> 30:27.042
WHEN I GOT
OUT OF THE HOSPITAL,

30:27.651 --> 30:29.479
PEOPLE WERE FRIGHTENED
BY THE WAY THAT I LOOKED.

30:31.046 --> 30:32.178
EVEN MY FRIENDS...

30:34.397 --> 30:35.790
DIDN'T KNOW WHAT TO SAY

30:36.573 --> 30:38.097
OR HOW TO BE AROUND ME.

30:42.231 --> 30:44.799
AND SO I, I LIVE HERE.

30:46.845 --> 30:47.802
ALONE.

30:48.585 --> 30:50.849
I FORCED MYSELF
TO STOP THINKING.

30:52.111 --> 30:53.677
STOP FEELING.

30:55.244 --> 30:56.550
OH, AND THEN I SAW YOU.

30:58.204 --> 31:00.380
YOU LOOK
SO MUCH LIKE CATHERINE.

31:05.515 --> 31:07.778
YOU MADE ME REMEMBER
HOW IT WAS TO FEEL LOVE.

31:24.491 --> 31:25.884
-BILLY: HE'S GOTTA BE
AROUND HERE SOMEWHERE.

31:26.014 --> 31:27.494
-BOBBY: I GUESS SO.
-HE MUST'VE GONE INSIDE.

31:27.624 --> 31:29.191
LET'S GO GET HIM.
DON'T FORGET THE FLASHLIGHT.

31:29.322 --> 31:30.410
-RIGHT HERE.
-GOOD.

31:35.676 --> 31:37.199
-I'M VERY MUCH LIKE POE.

31:37.330 --> 31:39.723
I THOUGHT I'D NEVER GET OVER
LOSING CATHERINE.

31:44.641 --> 31:46.469
THIS IS
THE FIRST TIME IN YEARS

31:47.383 --> 31:49.037
I FELT
AS IF I COULD LOVE AGAIN.

31:50.952 --> 31:51.822
-AIDEN...

31:56.697 --> 31:59.918
-I, I KNOW YOU
CAN'T LOVE ME, C.J.,

32:01.658 --> 32:03.399
BUT AT LEAST I KNOW
I CAN FEEL AGAIN.

32:04.574 --> 32:06.576
I THOUGHT THAT HAD
DIED IN THE FIRE, TOO.

32:07.229 --> 32:08.056
-AIDEN.

32:09.318 --> 32:10.972
LET ME SEE YOUR FACE.

32:11.103 --> 32:11.973
-NO.

32:12.756 --> 32:14.019
NO, I CAN'T.

32:14.802 --> 32:15.934
-PLEASE.

33:08.029 --> 33:09.204
-DON'T PITY ME.

33:10.945 --> 33:12.468
-I COULD NEVER
PITY YOU, AIDEN.

33:17.430 --> 33:18.779
I COULD ONLY ENVY YOU.

33:22.087 --> 33:25.220
BEING SO KIND, AND SO GENTLE.

33:27.483 --> 33:29.094
THE WAY
PEOPLE HAVE TREATED YOU,

33:30.486 --> 33:31.835
THEY'RE THE ONES THAT I PITY.

33:35.274 --> 33:37.319
IF THEY COULD LIVE WITH
WHAT YOU'VE HAD TO LIVE WITH

33:37.450 --> 33:38.886
FOR JUST ONE DAY,

33:39.495 --> 33:41.410
WEAR THIS ON THEIR OWN FACE,

33:43.934 --> 33:46.372
THEY MIGHT FINALLY BE ABLE
TO BE KIND TO EACH OTHER.

33:49.636 --> 33:53.031
NO, I'M THINKING OF HOW GOOD,

33:54.945 --> 33:55.990
AND HOW GENTLE,

33:58.297 --> 34:00.299
AND HOW BEAUTIFUL THIS MAN IS.

34:04.390 --> 34:05.260
[SQUAWKING]

34:05.913 --> 34:06.870
-SHH!

34:11.440 --> 34:13.529
WHOA, HE'S IN THERE!
HE'S GOT HER IN THERE!

34:13.659 --> 34:14.965
KILL THE LIGHTS!

34:15.096 --> 34:17.446
[CRASHING]
GOD, BOBBY, YOU MORON!

34:18.795 --> 34:19.969
WHY DON'T YOU JUST
TELL HIM WE'RE IN HERE?

34:20.101 --> 34:21.059
-STAY HERE.

34:27.717 --> 34:28.630
[GRUNTING]

34:28.762 --> 34:30.938
-NO!
-ALL RIGHT!

34:31.069 --> 34:31.938
HOLD HIM, BOYS!

34:32.070 --> 34:33.158
WHOA, EXCELLENT!

34:34.507 --> 34:35.856
[GRUNTING]

34:38.250 --> 34:39.380
-NO! STOP!

34:56.094 --> 34:57.747
-BILLY: THERE HE GOES!
LET'S GET HIM!

35:03.536 --> 35:04.537
-AIDEN!

35:07.061 --> 35:08.671
[GRUNTING]

35:10.238 --> 35:11.761
-BILLY: DON'T
LET HIM GET AWAY!

35:14.721 --> 35:15.896
-AIDEN!

35:20.988 --> 35:22.337
-MITCH: CODY,
GRAB THE FLASHLIGHT!

35:28.561 --> 35:30.215
-AH, MITCH,
SHE COULD BE ANYWHERE.

35:31.129 --> 35:32.304
-IF SHE'S IN THERE,
WE'LL FIND HER.

35:32.434 --> 35:33.261
COME ON!

35:35.872 --> 35:38.048
[PANTING]

35:48.058 --> 35:49.495
[GRUNTING]

35:49.625 --> 35:50.887
-BILLY: THAT'S IT, BOBBY!
COME ON, GET HIM!

35:58.808 --> 36:01.115
[GRUNTING]

36:04.249 --> 36:06.860
COME ON! GO, GO, GO!
GET OUT OF THE WAY!

36:08.340 --> 36:09.776
[PANTING]

36:18.828 --> 36:21.396
-C.J.!
-C.J.!

36:26.184 --> 36:28.664
-BILLY:
I GOT THIS FREAK NOW!

36:43.679 --> 36:46.116
COME ON! COME ON!
GET UP, YOU GUYS, LET'S GO!

37:00.827 --> 37:04.483
-C.J.!
-CODY!

37:04.613 --> 37:07.442
HURRY! UP HERE!

37:36.079 --> 37:37.646
-BILLY:
GRAB HIM! GRAB HIM!

37:38.908 --> 37:41.998
-NOW BILLY, WE GOT HIM!
-USE THE CHLOROFORM, WILL.

37:42.129 --> 37:45.350
WE ARE HERE LIVE, FILMING
THE CAPTURE OF A MONSTER.

37:45.480 --> 37:47.003
-I AM NOT A MONSTER!

37:47.700 --> 37:49.571
PLEASE, I WON'T HURT YOU!

37:50.398 --> 37:51.269
-NO!

37:55.011 --> 37:55.882
-WHOO!

37:56.012 --> 37:57.536
-DON'T HURT HIM!

38:00.539 --> 38:02.584
MITCH, YOU GOTTA GET HIM,
HE'S THE ONE WHO SAVED ME!

38:08.938 --> 38:09.939
AIDEN!

38:18.339 --> 38:20.515
[GRUNTING]

38:28.436 --> 38:29.785
-BOTH: MITCH!

39:06.518 --> 39:08.171
-AIDEN, I'M JUST
GLAD YOU'RE OK.

39:08.302 --> 39:09.303
-I AM NOW.

39:10.870 --> 39:12.698
-ALL RIGHT, LET'S GET HIM TO
THE HOSPITAL AND CHECKED OUT.

39:12.828 --> 39:13.916
-WAIT, PLEASE.

39:16.092 --> 39:17.311
-OFFICER: SIT RIGHT THERE.

39:17.442 --> 39:18.530
-AIDEN: THANK YOU.

39:18.660 --> 39:19.661
-IT'S OK.

39:19.792 --> 39:21.576
YOU'RE GONNA BE FINE.

39:21.707 --> 39:22.925
COME ON, LET'S GO.

39:25.885 --> 39:26.842
-PARAMEDIC: EASY.

39:28.931 --> 39:31.107
-SORRY I WASN'T
HERE FOR YOU, BABY.

39:31.717 --> 39:32.892
-THAT'S OK.

39:33.762 --> 39:35.721
JUST KISS MY KNEE AND
IT'LL FEEL BETTER.

39:39.202 --> 39:40.116
-HOW'S THAT?

39:40.247 --> 39:41.335
-MUCH BETTER.

39:42.292 --> 39:43.511
-SO UH, WHAT DO YOU SAY,

39:43.642 --> 39:45.383
A COUPLE
OF SETS OF MIXED DOUBLES, HUH?

39:45.513 --> 39:46.645
-VERY FUNNY.
[LAUGHING]

39:46.775 --> 39:48.081
-YOU'RE ON.
-ALL RIGHT.

39:48.211 --> 39:50.997
HOW ABOUT A LITTLE
OYSTERS, YOU KNOW?

39:51.127 --> 39:52.607
LITTLE SHRIMP ON THE BARBIE?
-CODY: GLADSTONES?

39:52.738 --> 39:53.565
-MITCH: GLADSTONES.

39:53.695 --> 39:54.957
-C.J.: I'M STARVING.

40:06.578 --> 40:08.449
-HEY, C.J.
-HI.

40:08.580 --> 40:11.017
-HOW'S AIDEN?
-OH, HE GOT A JOB AT UCLA.

40:11.147 --> 40:13.411
HE'S GONNA BE TEACHING
MISUNDERSTOOD POE.

40:13.541 --> 40:14.847
-OH, THAT'S GREAT.

40:14.977 --> 40:15.935
-AND HE FINALLY
GOT THE COURAGE

40:16.065 --> 40:17.589
TO GO SEE A PLASTIC SURGEON,

40:17.719 --> 40:19.068
AND HE HAD HIS
FIRST CONSULTATION

40:19.199 --> 40:20.461
FOR RECONSTRUCTIVE SURGERY.

40:23.072 --> 40:24.987
-LOOK, C.J.,
I'VE BEEN A REAL IDIOT.

40:25.640 --> 40:26.815
I HAVEN'T BEEN THINKING
ABOUT YOU AT ALL,

40:26.946 --> 40:28.861
AND UH, AND I'M SORRY.

40:30.689 --> 40:32.168
-WELL, IT'S NOT
THAT YOU HAVEN'T BEEN

40:32.299 --> 40:33.431
THINKING
ABOUT ME THAT HURTS.

40:34.475 --> 40:36.999
IT'S JUST THAT YOU HAVEN'T BEEN
THINKING ABOUT US VERY MUCH.

40:37.652 --> 40:38.479
-I AM NOW.

40:39.262 --> 40:40.263
MORE THAN EVER.

40:44.920 --> 40:46.356
I LOVE YOU SO MUCH, BABY.

40:48.010 --> 40:50.143
AND IF ANYTHING EVER
HAPPENED TO YOU, I...

40:51.753 --> 40:53.320
WELL, I COULD UNDERSTAND
HOW AIDEN WENT NUTS

40:53.451 --> 40:55.061
AFTER LOSING HIS WIFE.

40:57.498 --> 40:58.586
-WHAT'S THIS?

41:01.502 --> 41:02.851
-MARRY ME, C.J.

41:04.418 --> 41:05.811
I WANT YOU
TO BE MY WIFE.

41:16.822 --> 41:19.259
[CLOSING THEME PLAYING]
